etymologies: mid 19th century; earliest use found in Richard Owen (1804–1892), comparative anatomist and palaeontologist. From myxine + -oid

definitions: An agnathan (jawless) vertebrate of the group consisting of the extant hagfishes; a hagfish.

notes.text: The group has been called various names at several different ranks, but may be called Myxinoidea when ranked as a class or order.

definitions: Of, relating to, or characteristic of the hagfishes.
